In this interview, the President of the United States discusses various topics including the Buy America clause, NAFTA, oil sands, clean energy, Afghanistan, and his thoughts on Canada. He assures that protectionist policies will not be implemented, and that international trade agreements will be respected. He also acknowledges the importance of Canada as a trading partner and the need to balance economic growth with environmental concerns. In regards to Afghanistan, he emphasizes the need for a comprehensive strategy and the involvement of diplomacy and development, not just military means. The President praises Canada for its management of the financial system and economy during the economic crisis. He also expresses his admiration for Canada's diversity, natural beauty, and its ability to be a good manager of the financial system.